<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="choke-v">choke <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /tʃəʊk/    美 /tʃoʊk/  </p>
<p>vt &amp; vi</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>(使) 窒息；(使) 噎住；</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The smoke choked me.
烟呛得我喘不过气来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He choked when he ate his food too quickly.
他吃东西太快，噎住了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>（管子，渠道等）堵塞：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The pipe was choked up with leaves.
这条管子被树叶堵塞了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="choke-back">choke back</h3>
<p>1.<strong>强忍住；抑制</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Their story was so sad that I had to choke back sobs.
他们的故事是那么悲伤，我强忍住不抽泣。</p><footer>译林⑩-3</footer></div>

<h3 id="choke-off">choke off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>阻塞</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Unfortunately, the increased number of vehicles on the road choked off traffic.
不幸的是，马路上增加的车辆把道路堵得水泄不通。</p><footer>译林⑦-4</footer></div></div>